Interface Flushable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Log, Logger, SerializationSession
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface Flushable
    An object that can be flushed, like a queue or output stream.
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      default void flush()
      Flush the object, waiting until finished doing so.
      void flush​(Duration maximumWaitTime)
      Flushes the object waiting not more than the give duration for this to occur.

    • Method Detail

      • flush

        void flush​(Duration maximumWaitTime)
        Flushes the object waiting not more than the give duration for this to occur.
        Parameters:
        maximumWaitTime - The amount of time to wait before giving up on flushing. To achieve a blocking flush, simply pass in Duration.MAXIMUM as the wait time, or call flush().
